                  </hi>. I am constable of the Mendicity Society. On the 22nd of July I was on duty—I saw the prisoner cross Tottenham-court-road into Store-street—knowing him I followed him, with Daniels another officer, who stopped him, and took something from him, which was a pint pot—I then took a basket of pots from him, and said, "What are you going to do with these?"—he said, "l am a pewterer "—I said, "I know you are a pewter dealer"—I took him into a public-house, and found four pots in this basket.</p>
